<HEADLINE>
STARS' CAMP IMPRESSES HITCHCOCK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE HEIKA 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dallas Stars coach Ken Hitchcock left Vail, Colo., singing the
praises of the the team's work ethic.
</P>
<P>
   ``Personally, I think it's been the best training camp we've
had,'' said Hitchcock, completing his third camp with the team.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars wrapped up five days in Vail with an early practice,
but no scrimmage. Instead, they will have their final full-squad
scrimmage at 10 this morning at the Dr Pepper StarCenter in Irving.
</P>
<P>
   It likely will be the final appearance for several junior-league
players who will return to their junior teams Sunday. The Stars
also will send 23 players on the road for preseason exhibition
games to Sunday in Lakeland, Fla., and St. Louis on Monday. The
rest of the veterans will remain in Texas to prepare for a
preseason game Tuesday against the Nashville Predators in Little
Rock, Ark. FOREIGN COACH ASSISTS STARS
</P>
<P>
   The Stars have opened their training camp to Vladimir Jourzinov,
a longtime assistant coach in the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
   Jourzinov also has coached in Finland for several years and the
Stars have done a great deal of scouting in the country. Jourzinov,
who coached the Stars' Jere Lehtinen in Finland and Sergei Zubov in
the USSR, is in town for two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am not coaching, I am learning,'' Jourzinov said.
</P>
<P>
   But Hitchcock, who had a long discussion with Jourzinov through
a translator, said the veteran coach has great ideas.
</P>
<P>
   ``He has such an extensive background, there's just so much we
can learn from him,'' Hitchcock said. PARTNER SWITCHING
</P>
<P>
   Stars coaches are experimenting with several defensive pairs
during the preseason with Richard Matvichuk missing time to
rehabilitate his left knee and Darryl Sydor out because of a
contract dispute.
</P>
<P>
   Matvichuk regularly has been paired with Derian Hatcher, forming
the Stars' top defensive duo. Stars assistant coach Rick Wilson has
experimented with the duo of Hatcher and Shawn Chambers or rookie
Petr Buzek.
</P>
<P>
   Sydor has been paired with Sergei Zubov, forming the Stars' top
offensive duo. In camp, veteran Dan Keczmer has been paired with
Zubov.
</P>
<P>
   The third pair regularly has been veteran Craig Ludwig with
rookie Sergey Gusev.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a lot to look at,'' Wilson said. ``We'll probably need
all eight exhibition games to study everything.'' HITCHCOCK
PRESENTS
</P>
<P>
   The Stars announced last week they had signed Wilson and
assistant coach Doug Jarvis to three-year contract extensions. With
the earlier extension awarded to Hitchcock, the Stars could have
the same staff through 2001-02.
</P>
<P>
   ``What Rick and Doug do for me is they challenge me. If they
don't agree with something we're doing, they'll come after me,
they'll challenge me daily,'' Hitchcock said. ``They're very
supportive. But if they don't like something, they're not going to
let it slide. I find that kind of passion goes a long way, because
the players read how much the coaching staff cares about winning.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
