legislation that lets the government take over or shut down
crippled banks. By Sheryl WuDunn.
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMER-CONFIDENCE (Undated) _ In the midst of bad news from
Asia, Russia, Latin America and the Starr report, consumer
confidence remains resilient. By Sylvia Nasar.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Friday was a strange day on Wall Street.
Bond prices rallied, pushing down the yield on 30-year Treasury
bonds closer to 5 percent. But this flight by many investors to the
Treasury's safe harbor did not come at the expense of stock prices,
as it has done recently. By Jonathan Fuerbringer.
