<P>
   EUROPE-ECON (Rome) _ As dismal news emanates from around the
globe, European economies are proving remarkably resilient. But
evidence is growing that the continent's 2-year old recovery is
coming under strain, fueling debate about what can be done to
shield Europe from the effects of the turmoil. By John Tagliabue.
