<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Sept. 20 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LA-AEROSPACE-GROWTH (Palmdale, Calif.) _ While other parts of
Southern California continue to be hit with large-scale layoffs by
aerospace companies, there is a feeling of optimism about the
industry in the Antelope Valley in north Los Angeles county. Gone
are the large production programs for military aircraft that have
been the Antelope Valley aerospace industry's bread and butter for
years. Filling that void now are space endeavors, aircraft
prototyping and subassembly work. By Jim Skeen. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DEAD-COP-STORY (Los Angeles) _ Years after he was gunned down in
the line of duty, a North Hollywood police officer is being removed
from a pauper's grave, getting a headstone and proper burial thanks
to a local resident who stumbled on the slain officer's story. By
Dennis McCarthy. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
