<HEADLINE>
WHEATLEY IS IN UNDER THE SCALE 
</HEADLINE>
  (See also FBN-GIANTS-MONDAY) 
(bl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ The New York Giants weighed running back
Tyrone Wheatley before Saturday's practice and he was more than a
pound below the 235 pounds he played at last season, a goal that
coach Jim Fassel had set for Wheatley last week.
</P>
<P>
   Fassel said Saturday that he expected Wheatley, who was held out
of last week's game because of his weight, to play Monday against
the Dallas Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to go into a Wheatley watch,'' Fassel said.
``But he's right on target for what I want him to do.''
</P>
<P>
   The Giants only weigh players on a weekly basis two days before
a game. Team officials would not be specific about Wheatley's
weight. Wheatley has run on a treadmill after practice throughout
the week.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told Tyrone Monday I want you do this,'' Fassel said
Saturday. ``He said: `I can't do that.' I said: `You're going to
have to do that.' His lesson in life is don't say you can't.''
</P>
</TEXT>
