<P>
   BASS-TOUR _ MOLINE, ILL. _ Final-day coverage of Wal-Mart FLW
Tour Championships. (Bernarde, Atlanta Journa-Constitution) 12.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BASS-FANS _ MOLINE, ILL. _ What makes someone a bass fishing
fan? It's not like you can watch a tournament in a stadium or at a
field, but thousands will flock to a Wal-Mart parking lot in
Moline, Ill., to watch the weigh-in each day for the FLW Tour World
Championship. The final weigh-in is done under a big top tent that
is transformed into a TV studio (there are even commercial breaks).
Around 1,500 to 2,000 fans are allowed in the ``studio'' for the
weigh-ins, but many, many more are outside. Similar to NASCAR fans,
they'll buy the products their favorite angler endorses. Fans at
home get to watch a made-for-TV event as television coverage jumps
from angler to angler, similar to golf coverage. (Bernarde, Atlanta
Journa-Constitution) 20-25.
</P>
