<P>
   SHERMOBIT _ Robert W. Sherman, the first president of The Palm
Beach Post and its sister publications after they were acquired by
Cox Enterprises, died early Saturday. He was 88. Mr. Sherman
devoted 50 years to the newspaper business, starting as a
classified ad salesman for the Dayton Daily News in 1928 at age 18.
He retired Jan. 1, 1979, as executive vice president and a member
of the board of directors of the Atlanta-based chain which now owns
16 daily newspapers -- including ones in Atlanta, Dayton and Austin
_ and 11 weeklies. (O'Meilia/Cooper, Palm Beach Post). 15-18. WITH
FILE MUG.
</P>
