<HEADLINE>
HARDEMAN SUSPENDED INDEFINITELY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HATTIESBURG, Miss. _ Texas A&AMP;M senior fullback D'Andre Hardeman,
the Aggies' leading scorer and rusher this season, has been
suspended indefinitely from the team, school officials announced
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   No reason was given. He did not travel to the Aggies' game with
Southern Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wish I could, but I can't elaborate,'' coach R.C. Slocum
said. ``And I can't say when it will be resolved.''
</P>
<P>
   School officials earlier had said Hardeman missed the first
three days of practice this week because of illness, but said he
was at practice on Thursday in shorts. A&AMP;M's key short-yardage
runner, the 234-pound back had scored four touchdowns in two games
this season to bring his career total to 30, seventh-best in school
history. Hardeman also led the Aggies with 105 yards on 24 carries.
</P>
