</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: Arizona Diamondbacks
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 4:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Bank One Ballpark.
</P>
<P>
   TV/Radio: TBS, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Bruce Chen (1-0, 5.79; first
appearance vs. Diamondbacks) vs. RHP Amaury Telemaco (6-9, 3.61;
1-1, 3.29 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Chen is making his third major start and his first as
Kevin Millwood's replacement in the rotation, as Millwood assumes a
spot in the bullpen. The rookie defeated Florida 4-2 last Saturday
for his first victory and while he has been hit in his two
appearances (12 hits in 9 1/3 innings), he continues to strike out
opponents at a high rate with 12. Telemaco has been a staple of
Arizona's rotation after being picked up on waivers from the
Chicago Cubs in June. He has the lowest ERA among the starters
after Omar Daal's 2.70, but has done so with good damage control.
Telemaco has allowed 140 hits and walked 41 in 135 innings this
year but yielded just 69 runs. The Braves catch him after one of
his weakest efforts. He lasted just 3 1/3 innings against San
Francisco last Tuesday, giving up six runs on five hits. He has
worked past the sixth inning just six times in 16 starts.
</P>
